Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Halve the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} widthways. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Crush the @Salted Peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g} and fry until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.
> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, add the broccoli and @Egg Noodle Nest{2} to the pan of boiling water.

Simmer until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop the noodles sticking together and keep the veg vibrant.

Once the beef mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.
> The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @Water for the Sauce{75%ml}, @Bulgogi Sauce{150%g} and @Soy Sauce{15%ml}. Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly reduced, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the cooked noodles and broccoli to the beef.

Toss to coat and add a splash of @?water{1%splash} if you feel it needs it, then heat through until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed.

When everything's ready, serve your bulgogi beef noodles in #bowls{}.

Sprinkle the peanuts over the top to finish. Enjoy!